1182":"1182","1170":"1170","1249":"1249","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","about 1220":"about 1220","Oxmuir, Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Castle Acre, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Castle Acre, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Harthill, Yorkshire, England":"Harthill, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":50,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Bosvil of Oxmuir was born about 1165, in Harthill, Yorkshire, England, his father, Sir Elias de Bosvil of Harthill, was 47 and his mother, Alice de Newmarch, was 27. He had at least 1 son. He died about 1220, in Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 57."},"et":{"abt 1165–about 1220":"umbes 1165–umbes 1220","1165–1220":"1165–1220","1170–Female":"1170–Surnud","1174–1235":"1174–1235","1176–Female":"1176–Surnud","1205–1249":"1205–1249","1120–1182":"1120–1182","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1176":"1176","1220":"1220","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","abt 1165":"umbes 1165","1182":"1182","1170":"1170","1249":"1249","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","about 1220":"umbes 1220","Oxmuir, Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Hume, Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Castle Acre, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Castle Acre, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Harthill, Yorkshire, England":"Harthill, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"abt 1165–about 1220":"noin 1165–noin 1220","1165–1220":"1165–1220","1170–Female":"1170–Kuollut","1174–1235":"1174–1235","1176–Female":"1176–Kuollut","1205–1249":"1205–1249","1120–1182":"1120–1182","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1176":"1176","1220":"1220","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","abt 1165":"noin 1165","1182":"1182","1170":"1170","1249":"1249","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","about 1220":"noin 1220","Oxmuir, Hume, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Hume, Berwickshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Castle Acre, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Castle Acre, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Harthill, Yorkshire, England":"Harthill, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"abt 1165–about 1220":"environ 1165–environ 1220","1165–1220":"1165–1220","1170–Female":"1170–Décédée","1174–1235":"1174–1235","1176–Female":"1176–Décédée","1205–1249":"1205–1249","1120–1182":"1120–1182","1140–Female":"1140–Décédée","1176":"1176","1220":"1220","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1174":"1174","1140":"11